data.jamchart_notes: Hailing from Canada after its longest gap in several years, this "Hoserwood" delivers "Rosewood's" finest performance since at least the Cap in 2024. Immediately launching into an upbeat, high-energy, hose jam imbued with a bluesy, Allman-esque rock vibe, it eventually downshifts to near silence. From there, a thundering percussive segment builds with a Middle Eastern-accented theme reminiscent of a "Tumble" jam, ultimately ending rather abruptly and unceremoniously.

Second-longest jam in the band's history (to date) is really all about the 20+ minute exploration of a single idea - searing, choppy funk with Rick in power stance. When it finally peaks, it's absolutely VOLCANIC.
